text: the new 'live coding' thing would be impressive if i didnt have Jrebel running
<@U0D8P42SC>: JRebel or the Live Coding? I tried JRebel and it just crashed my phone so hard it rebooted.
Now I don't have the money to pay for it. It's too expensive for what I can use it for as a single developer and startup.

Founded in 2010, Turkish mobile games developer Peak Games started developing games targeted to the local market and is now scaling globally. Their game <https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=net.peakgames.mobile.spades.android&hl=en_GB|‘Spades Plus>’ is growing in the US and the game generates over 70% of its mobile revenue from Android.

Available in more than 190 countries, Google Play is a global platform for developers to build high quality apps and successful businesses.
